<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Describes a spatial relation where two regions are strictly disjoint and share no spatial points."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "disconnected"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "disjoint regions"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/DC> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Angband and Doriath are disconnected since they share no spatial regions."@en .
# 
# https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#ObjectProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/location/borders> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#subPropertyOf> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/spatiallyRelatedTo> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#SymmetricProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#type> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#IrreflexiveProperty> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#propertyDisjointWith> <https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/NTPP> .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment> "Denotes a relation where the boundaries of two regions intersect while their interiors remain disjoint."@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label> "externally connected"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "touching regions"@en .
<https://w3id.org/narn/rcc/EC> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#example> "Brethil is externally connected to Doriath because their boundaries touch."@en .
# 
